summary: Good Omens. Episode 1: In The Beginning. Gifset 1/? I’ve decided to post a gifset every Wednesday, because I anticipate needing...
caption:
Good Omens. Episode 1: In The Beginning. Gifset 1/?

I’ve decided to post a gifset every Wednesday, because I anticipate needing a boost to my serotonin levels, and Good Omens is doing a splendid job of that so far. 

I love Crowley mostly always being on Aziraphale’s left hand side, because that’s where we get the word sinister from, before it came to mean “evil” or “unlucky”. 

And Aziraphale is so adorable. I think I make some of those faces whenever someone talks to me in a social setting. So proud when he thinks of something intellectual to say.

summary: Crowley and Aziraphale’s eating habits (Btw, these are the kinds of discussions you start having after watching the show several...
caption:
Crowley and Aziraphale’s eating habits (Btw, these are the kinds of discussions you start having after watching the show several times)

So my friend and I were re-watching this and he asked “Why it is that you never see Crowley eating? Does he just not eat?” My response was that Crowley enjoys a good meal as much as anyone, Aziraphale just tends to eat much slower, wanting to savor every bite. So basically by the time Aziraphale is finished, Crowley is way past done with his meal, on his second cup of coffee and has already asked for the check.

To which of course we both agreed that those scenes probably sucked for David cause he had to sit there while Michael got to enjoy all the goodies.

summary: My mother: fangirl work in progress pt.2
body:
My mother: fangirl work in progress pt.2

Yes, I said that this would become a series and here we are!

Today, I’m in hospital. Nothing serious but I felt too hurt even to read, so I asked my mun to read for me Good Omens.

We have already watched three episode from the mini series, but she didn’t remember much and, naturally, the book is quite different from the tv show.

I had to explain Pollution, because “Who is this Mr. White?”. Then I found out that she can’t say Aziraphale (or, to be honest, the Italian version Azraphel) so she started to read it as Raphael.

Then she laughed a lot about Aziraphale eating devilled eggs and Crowley eating angel cake.

In the end, she was a little… well… WTF, when during the Warlock’s birthday, Aziraphale accidentally started a shooting.

“Was Crowley at the party too?”

“Yes mum. He was in the back of the gazebo, weating all white…”

“I can remember. I think we should watch again all of it, from the start”

Thank mum for this rewatching, thank you.
